          "content": "The forum confirms the exact issue. Our token has `\"scopes\": []` — the OAuth client in GLPI is not granting the `api` scope when issuing tokens, even though the user has the right profile.\n\nThe fix is in the **OAuth client config in GLPI**, not the user profile. In GLPI web UI:\n\n1. Go to **Setup → OAuth Applications** (or **Administration → OAuth Applications** depending on version)\n2. Open client `5880211c...`\n3. Find **\"Allowed scopes\"** or **\"Scopes\"** — make sure `api` is **checked/enabled** there\n4. Save\n\nThe key difference from the forum thread: the user in that thread got `\"scopes\": [\"api\"]` in their JWT. Ours has `\"scopes\": []` — meaning GLPI is issuing the token but stripping all scopes, which means the client app itself doesn't have those scopes allowed.\n\nOnce you save that in the OAuth client config, the token will include `\"scopes\": [\"api\"]` and all the 403s will disappear."
